download the map area from bbbike


You need to do this twice: once for GraphHopper (Routing) and once for TileServer-GL (3D Graphics).
1. Get the Small Routing File (For GraphHopper)

    Go to extract.bbbike.org in your web browser.

    Under the Format dropdown, select Protocolbuffer (PBF).

    Type "Thiruvananthapuram" into the search bar to move the map.

    Click the "Here" button to generate a bounding box. Drag the corners so it covers the exact area your emergency vehicles will operate in (e.g., covering Technopark down to Kowdiar).

    Enter your email address and click Extract.

    In about 2 minutes, you will get an email with a link to download your tiny .osm.pbf file (it will likely be less than 10MB!). Rename this file to southern-zone-latest.osm and put it in your ~/v2x_routing folder.
    
   
  2. Get the Small 3D Graphics File (For TileServer-GL)

    Go right back to the BBBike website with your box still drawn.

    Change the Format dropdown to MBTiles (OpenMapTiles). (This is crucial—this format contains the 3D mathematical vectors required by our PyQt UI).

    Click Extract again.

    Download the file, rename it to trivandrum.mbtiles, and place it in your ~/v2x_routing folder.


Run the command to start the graphhopper server
    java -Xmx2g -jar graphhopper-web-8.0.jar server config.yml
(you can also make this into a service or run this on a seprate terminal every time )


